text: Lampart Futball Club is a Hungarian football club from the town of Budapest. ==History== Lampart FC debuted in the 1941–42 season of the Hungarian League and finished ninth. == Name Changes == *1937–1938: FÉG-Lampart *1938: merger with Erzsébet FC *1938–1943: Lampart FC *1943–1945: Fegyvergyári SK *1945–1948: Lampart SE *1948: merger with Pasaréti SE *1948–1951: Lampart MSK *1951–1952: Vasas Lampart SK *1952–1957: Vasas Kőbányai Zománc *1957–?:Lampart SE == References == ==External links== * Profile Category:Football clubs in Hungary Category:1937 establishments in Hungary
title: Lampart FC
